
[1]amicable

   AM'ICABLE, a. [L. amicabilis, from amicus, a friend, from amo, to
   love.]

   1. Friendly; peaceable; harmonious in social or mutual transactions;
   usually applied to the dispositions of men who have business with each
   other, or to their intercourse and transactions; as, nations or men
   have come to an amicable adjustment of their differences.

   2. Disposed to peace and friendship; as, an amicable temper. [But
   rarely applied to a single person.]
